00:23:54.578 --> 00:23:59.170
But the effect,
if she has the right people

00:23:59.170 --> 00:24:04.150
doing it and trusts them,
is very like Adam Smith's pin

00:24:04.150 --> 00:24:08.190
factory and the division of
labor and the power it produces.

00:24:08.190 --> 00:24:13.076
So we're back to Smith;
Smith had the idea that by

00:24:13.076 --> 00:24:18.181
dividing labor so that one
person doesn't undertake the

00:24:18.181 --> 00:24:22.528
whole complex task of
manufacturing a pin,

00:24:22.528 --> 00:24:26.531
if you divide the labor among
many who get good at specific

00:24:26.531 --> 00:24:29.785
aspects of the task,
you can make it cheaper and

00:24:29.785 --> 00:24:32.868
more efficient then otherwise it
would have been.

00:24:32.868 --> 00:24:35.910
Hayek's idea is more loosely
jointed than that.

00:24:35.910 --> 00:24:41.970
Hayek's idea is that you don't
even assign roles to people;

00:24:41.970 --> 00:24:43.818
you let them find their own
roles.

00:24:43.818 --> 00:24:50.557
That if you want to go out and
start a toothbrush factory using

00:24:50.557 --> 00:24:55.497
a novel technology,
invented late at night over

00:24:55.497 --> 00:25:01.108
beer with your roommate,
what's the likely outcome?

00:25:01.108 --> 00:25:06.180
The likely outcome is that you
will fail.

00:25:06.180 --> 00:25:10.170
Your toothbrush will be too
expensive and not very good.

00:25:10.170 --> 00:25:11.599
Right?
 

00:25:11.599 --> 00:25:13.140
Isn't that the likely thing?
 

00:25:13.140 --> 00:25:18.847
If you think about a market
economy as literally hundreds of

00:25:18.847 --> 00:25:23.880
thousands of people who make
decisions like that--

00:25:23.880 --> 00:25:27.308
go/ no go--with a new model
toothbrush,

00:25:27.308 --> 00:25:34.380
the accumulated knowledge from
that is enormously powerful.

00:25:34.380 --> 00:25:40.048
If you begin to make money with
your new model toothbrush,

00:25:40.048 --> 00:25:43.828
then a couple of things will
happen.

00:25:43.828 --> 00:25:47.170
One, capital will flow toward
you.

00:25:47.170 --> 00:25:50.119
People will say,
we would like to own part of

00:25:50.119 --> 00:25:50.588
this.
 

00:25:50.588 --> 00:25:54.407
And our subject next Monday is
the joint stock corporation,

00:25:54.407 --> 00:25:56.118
which is all about that.
 

00:25:56.118 --> 00:26:02.740
And capital will flow toward
you, and so will competition.

00:26:02.740 --> 00:26:08.211
As soon as you begin to succeed
people will attempt to get as

00:26:08.211 --> 00:26:13.045
close to your product as the
patent and copyright laws

00:26:13.045 --> 00:26:16.712
permit,
and to compete with you on the

00:26:16.712 --> 00:26:19.028
basis of quality or price.
 

00:26:19.028 --> 00:26:22.551
And that process,
you can think of it is as

00:26:22.551 --> 00:26:27.009
enormous diversified portfolio;
the whole economy.

00:26:27.009 --> 00:26:30.001
No one directs the whole
economy or says where the

00:26:30.001 --> 00:26:32.689
capital goes,
though sometimes it feels as if

00:26:32.689 --> 00:26:35.009
Goldman Sachs comes close to
that.

00:26:35.009 --> 00:26:44.490
The decision process is highly
decentralized and un-programmed.

00:26:44.490 --> 00:26:48.276
Indeed, Hayek,
if you'll look closely,

00:26:48.276 --> 00:26:54.622
says that what we're trying to
do is create the opportunity for

00:26:54.622 --> 00:26:57.588
the unexpected to happen.
 

00:26:57.588 --> 00:27:02.776
"Liberty is essential in
order to leave room for the

00:27:02.776 --> 00:27:05.740
unforeseeable and unpredicted.
 

00:27:05.740 --> 00:27:08.846
We want it because we have
learned to expect from it the

00:27:08.846 --> 00:27:11.670
opportunity of realizing many of
our aims."

00:27:11.670 --> 00:27:22.380
The core idea is disbursed
power of action.

00:27:22.380 --> 00:27:29.064
Now Hayek is entirely dependent
on the idea that we are of

00:27:29.064 --> 00:27:31.410
limited intellect.
 

00:27:31.410 --> 00:27:36.373
If we were, as this quote says,
omniscient, page 29,

00:27:36.373 --> 00:27:41.336
the green quote here,
there would not be so strong a

00:27:41.336 --> 00:27:43.380
case for freedom.
 

00:27:43.380 --> 00:27:44.920
I think there would be other
cases,

00:27:44.920 --> 00:27:49.904
but the core case that Hayek is
making is that freedom is a way

00:27:49.904 --> 00:27:52.880
of overcoming our own
fallibility,

00:27:52.880 --> 00:27:58.673
and of allowing others to fill
the holes in our individual

00:27:58.673 --> 00:28:00.910
stores of knowledge.
 

00:28:00.910 --> 00:28:06.762
Now Hayek, early in the section
you read, focuses on the

00:28:06.762 --> 00:28:09.848
question of a rock climber.
 

00:28:09.848 --> 00:28:21.336
It's kind of a jarring
reference when you see it,

00:28:21.336 --> 00:28:27.558
it's around page twelve.
 

00:28:27.558 --> 00:28:31.221
I read, "Most people will
still have enough feeling for

00:28:31.221 --> 00:28:35.068
the original meaning of the word
free to see that if"--

00:28:35.068 --> 00:28:40.218
no, sorry--"In this sense
freedom refers solely to the

00:28:40.218 --> 00:28:43.680
relation of men to other
men,"--

00:28:43.680 --> 00:28:47.556
or persons to other persons,
"The only infringement of

00:28:47.556 --> 00:28:49.160
it is coercion by men.
 

00:28:49.160 --> 00:28:52.087
This means, in particular that
the range of physical

00:28:52.087 --> 00:28:55.188
possibilities from which a
person can choose at a given

00:28:55.188 --> 00:28:57.828
moment has no direct relevance
to freedom.

00:28:57.828 --> 00:29:02.049
The rock climber on a difficult
pitch who sees only one way out

00:29:02.049 --> 00:29:04.910
to save his life is
unquestionably free.

00:29:04.910 --> 00:29:08.666
Most people will still have
enough feeling for the original

00:29:08.666 --> 00:29:12.554
meaning of the word free to see
that if the same rock climber

00:29:12.554 --> 00:29:16.634
were to fall into a crevasse and
were unable to get out he would

00:29:16.634 --> 00:29:19.680
only figuratively be called
unfree."

00:29:19.680 --> 00:29:24.940
Now that's a big--a lot rides
on that claim.

00:29:24.940 --> 00:29:30.009
Hayek defends it unevenly.
 

00:29:30.009 --> 00:29:32.970
If you look closely at the way
he defines coercion,

00:29:32.970 --> 00:29:38.817
you'll find that the rock
climber story is the clear and

00:29:38.817 --> 00:29:42.011
easy case,
and by the end of our slides

00:29:42.011 --> 00:29:44.545
today,
we'll begin to look at some

00:29:44.545 --> 00:29:49.097
harder cases and some of those
hard cases are raised by The

00:29:49.097 --> 00:29:50.890
White Tiger book.
 

00:29:50.890 --> 00:29:55.390
Now this is more my kind of
rock climber,

00:29:55.390 --> 00:29:57.640
