00:30:01.809 --> 00:30:07.319
What's behind this story?
 

00:30:07.319 --> 00:30:11.180
What--Hayek isn't sneaky here.
 

00:30:11.180 --> 00:30:14.048
Anybody want to tell us why he
makes this argument?

00:30:14.048 --> 00:30:22.645
Because he is arguing in an
environment where Communism is a

00:30:22.645 --> 00:30:29.000
very live option,
and the Marxist position about

00:30:29.000 --> 00:30:34.048
freedom is that it's a Bourgeois
delusion,

00:30:34.048 --> 00:30:41.298
and that only by giving
everyone the same access to

00:30:41.298 --> 00:30:48.670
material rewards,
to money, wealth, and the like;

00:30:48.670 --> 00:30:52.174
only by downward redistribution
of money, wealth,

00:30:52.174 --> 00:30:56.118
and the like can real freedom
be shared by everyone.

00:30:56.118 --> 00:31:01.058
Hayek wants desperately to head
off that argument.

00:31:01.058 --> 00:31:06.857
Now, whether that argument is
right or wrong is actually more

00:31:06.857 --> 00:31:12.559
semantic than anything else,
and we'll actually close with a

00:31:12.559 --> 00:31:14.588
slide about this.
 

00:31:14.588 --> 00:31:18.553
That is to say,
can you be free and at the

00:31:18.553 --> 00:31:23.000
bottom of society,
unable to do many things?

00:31:23.000 --> 00:31:28.430
Unable to effectively exercise
your freedom;

00:31:28.430 --> 00:31:33.086
one view is that the two
dimensions, freedom and wealth

00:31:33.086 --> 00:31:36.190
or power are entirely
independent.

00:31:36.190 --> 00:31:41.828
Another view is that without
some degree of market power,

00:31:41.828 --> 00:31:46.549
some degree of ability to
interest others in your needs

00:31:46.549 --> 00:31:51.708
through exchanging your skills
and your labor for what it is

00:31:51.708 --> 00:31:55.596
that you need,
or for the money which will buy

00:31:55.596 --> 00:31:58.038
what it is that you need or
want;

00:31:58.038 --> 00:32:03.521
only with some degree of market
power can freedom be fully

00:32:03.521 --> 00:32:04.579
realized.
 

00:32:04.579 --> 00:32:06.150
And I'm of that second view.
 

00:32:06.150 --> 00:32:12.068
I am of the view that the wide
dispersion of relative affluence

00:32:12.068 --> 00:32:15.220
