00:44:38.311 --> 00:44:42.949
near Rio in Brazil,
and it's all informal property.

00:44:42.949 --> 00:44:46.670
The people who built those
houses don't really own them.

00:44:46.670 --> 00:44:49.777
They own them according to a
set of informal rules that

00:44:49.777 --> 00:44:52.539
operate among the people in the
favela.

00:44:52.539 --> 00:44:58.025
They don't have formal
documentation for them,

00:44:58.025 --> 00:45:01.559
so it is informal property.
 

00:45:01.559 --> 00:45:07.458
Every building in New Haven is
formal property,

00:45:07.458 --> 00:45:13.230
even community gardens are
formal property.

00:45:13.230 --> 00:45:15.918
There is a deed written down,
you can trace it,

00:45:15.918 --> 00:45:17.789
and you can show it to a bank.
 

00:45:17.789 --> 00:45:29.971
de Soto's major idea is that
informal property is dead

00:45:29.971 --> 00:45:35.483
capital,
and formal property where the

00:45:35.483 --> 00:45:42.170
